Round_Rock.Pflugerville High School:
Pflugerville High School is a public high school located in Pflugerville, Texas that serves approximately 2,200 students from grades 9-12.

=== History ===


==== Football ====
During the 2013 NFL Draft, Pflugerville High School graduate Zaviar Gooden and Alex Okafor were drafted by the Tennessee Titans and Arizona Cardinals respectively.


===== 55-game winning streak =====
From 1958 until 1962, Pflugerville won 55 consecutive games.
